The President met with General John Allen and Ambassador Brett McGurk to discuss the importance of coordinating with allies and partners to build a strong coalition against ISIL. The President emphasized the need for a comprehensive approach involving political, diplomatic, military, economic, and other efforts to degrade and ultimately destroy ISIL. He also expressed his gratitude for the work and sacrifices of U.S. servicemen and women and diplomats involved in countering ISIL. The President thanked General Allen for his years of service in the military and his continued dedication to serving his country in a civilian capacity.